               <msContents>
                  <summary>Beginning of a letter from Demophon to Ptolemaeus.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Text is on one side only, 7 lines written with the fibers.  Top and left margins are visible.  Black paint on the reverse side.  Text mentions locations of Isieios and Talaos.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>7.6 X 4.0cm. Evidence of tearing along the bottom of the fragment.  Large tear on the middle left side obscures some writing.  Shows evidence of water damage.</p>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate when="-0245">245 BCE</origDate>
                     <origPlace>Hibeh, Mummy A9</origPlace>
